data.title: The “First Neighborhood”: Presidents and Preservation in Lafayette Park
data.listingDescription: Presidents from Franklin D. Roosevelt to Lyndon B. Johnson, as well as two first ladies, were instrumental in preserving the 19th century historic character of Lafayette Square. Their advocacy influenced not only the White House's closest national historic district, but the development of national historic preservation law.

listingImage.altText: Historic town homes in front of modern brick building
